text: The Kazincbarcika District (Hungarian: Kazincbarcikai járás) is a district in the northeastern part of Borsod-Abaúj-Zemplén County. Kazincbarcika is also the name of the town where the district seat is found. Its population in 2022 was 58,445. == Municipalities == The district has 3 town, 2 large villages and 17 villages. * Alacska * Alsótelekes * Bánhorváti * Berente * Dédestapolcsány * Felsőtelekes * Izsófalva * Kazincbarcika – district seat * Kurityán * Mályinka * Múcsony * Nagybarca * Ormosbánya * Rudabánya * Rudolftelep * Sajógalgóc * Sajóivánka * Sajókaza * Sajószentpéter * Szuhakálló * Tardona * Vadna The bolded municipalities are cities, italics municipalities are large villages.
